# FlexFlow — Supabase Auth & Integration Best Practices

Applies to all code in `supabase/` and any Flutter code that touches auth, remote data, or RLS.
When uncertain about anything, consult the [Supabase Auth docs](https://supabase.com/docs/guides/auth) or the NotebookLM notebook (UUID `3696ed17-acaf-4931-9f6a-a5d69e27cd01`).

**Target platforms: Android (primary) and Web. iOS is out of scope — do not add iOS-specific setup without explicit instruction.**

---

## Auth provider

FlexFlow uses **Google OAuth exclusively**. Never introduce another provider or email/password auth without explicit discussion.

---

## Google Sign-In — platform-specific flows

The sign-in method differs by platform. **Never use the wrong method for a platform.**

### Android — native `signInWithIdToken`

Use `google_sign_in` to get an OIDC ID token from the native account picker, then pass it to Supabase. This avoids opening a browser.

```dart
// ✅ Android
final googleUser = await GoogleSignIn(
  serverClientId: '<WEB_CLIENT_ID>',
).signIn();
final googleAuth = await googleUser!.authentication;

await supabase.auth.signInWithIdToken(
  provider: OAuthProvider.google,
  idToken: googleAuth.idToken!,
  accessToken: googleAuth.accessToken,
);
```

**Dashboard requirements (Android):**
- Add the Web Client ID under Authentication → Providers → Google.
- Register an Android Client ID in Google Cloud Console (package name + SHA-1 fingerprint).

### Web — `signInWithOAuth` redirect

`google_sign_in`'s native flow is not available on Flutter Web. Use the OAuth redirect flow instead.

```dart
// ✅ Web
await supabase.auth.signInWithOAuth(
  OAuthProvider.google,
  redirectTo: 'https://yourapp.com/auth/callback', // deployed URL
  // For local dev: 'http://localhost:PORT/auth/callback'
);
```

Add all redirect URLs (prod and dev) to the Supabase Dashboard's **Redirect URLs** allow-list.

### Sign out (all platforms)

```dart
// ✅ Sign out
await supabase.auth.signOut();

// ❌ Never implement email/password auth
supabase.auth.signInWithPassword(...); // FORBIDDEN
```

