## Deep links

Deep links are used on **Android** to route the user back into the app after a web-based OAuth fallback flow.

- Register `io.supabase.flexflow://login-callback/` in the Supabase Dashboard Redirect URL allow-list.
- Add an intent filter in `android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml` for the `io.supabase.flexflow` scheme.
- Add `<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.INTERNET" />` for production Android builds.
- `supabase_flutter` handles deep-link routing internally via `app_links` — do not add a second handler.

**Web** uses real HTTPS redirect URLs — no custom scheme or deep-link config required.

**iOS** deep-link setup (`Info.plist`) is not needed until iOS support is added — do not implement it proactively.

