## API keys — use new format

Legacy `anon` / `service_role` keys are **deprecated at end of 2026**. Always use the new key names.

| Key | Format | Where |
|---|---|---|
| Publishable key | `sb_publishable_xxx` | Flutter client — safe to bundle |
| Secret key | `sb_secret_xxx` | Edge Functions / server-side **only** |

The secret key bypasses RLS entirely — treat it as a root credential. Never expose it to the Flutter client or commit it to source control.

```dart
// ✅ Initialize with the publishable key
await Supabase.initialize(
  url: const String.fromEnvironment('SUPABASE_URL'),
  anonKey: const String.fromEnvironment('SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY'),
  localStorage: const SecureStorage(), // see secure storage section
);

// ✅ Access the singleton anywhere
final supabase = Supabase.instance.client;
```

Pass keys via `--dart-define` — never hardcode them in source files.

