## Secure token storage

Storage behaviour differs by platform:

| Platform | Default | Production |
|---|---|---|
| Android | `SharedPreferences` | `flutter_secure_storage` (Android Keystore) |
| Web | Browser `localStorage` | Default is acceptable — no native keychain on web |

For Android production, override with a custom `LocalStorage` backed by `flutter_secure_storage`:

```dart
// ✅ Android secure storage
class SecureStorage extends LocalStorage {
  final _storage = const FlutterSecureStorage();

  @override Future<void> initialize() async {}

  @override Future<String?> accessToken() =>
      _storage.read(key: supabaseAccessTokenKey);

  @override Future<bool> hasAccessToken() =>
      _storage.containsKey(key: supabaseAccessTokenKey);

  @override Future<void> persistSession(String s) =>
      _storage.write(key: supabaseAccessTokenKey, value: s);

  @override Future<void> removePersistedSession() =>
      _storage.delete(key: supabaseAccessTokenKey);
}
```

