## Token verification (Edge Functions)

Every protected Edge Function **must** call `getAuthenticatedUser(req)` from `supabase/ref/auth.ts` as its first action. It verifies the JWT server-side via `supabase.auth.getUser(token)` and throws `AuthenticationError` on any failure.

```typescript
// ✅ Always verify first
const user = await getAuthenticatedUser(req);
// user.userId and user.email are now trustworthy

// ❌ Never trust user IDs from the request body
const { userId } = await req.json(); // DO NOT use for auth decisions
```

