## CORS (Edge Functions)

Handle `OPTIONS` preflight before any other logic, and attach CORS headers to every response.

```typescript
// ✅ Always first in the handler
if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') {
  return handleCorsPreflightRequest(req);
}

// ✅ Attach on every response
return jsonResponse(data, { status: 200, headers: getCorsHeaders(req) });
```

Use the `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` env var to restrict origins in production. Never leave `*` in a production function unless the endpoint is intentionally public.

---

## Error handling (Edge Functions)

Use typed error classes from `ref/errors.ts`. Never swallow errors silently.

```typescript
// ✅ Throw typed errors
throw new AuthenticationError('Invalid or expired token'); // → 401
throw new BadRequestError('Missing required field');       // → 400
throw new ForbiddenError('You do not own this resource');  // → 403
throw new NotFoundError('Session not found');              // → 404

// ✅ Top-level catch
} catch (err) {
  if (err instanceof HttpError) {
    return jsonResponse({ error: err.message }, { status: err.status, headers: getCorsHeaders(req) });
  }
  console.error('Unhandled:', err);
  return jsonResponse({ error: 'Internal server error' }, { status: 500, headers: getCorsHeaders(req) });
}
```

