## Sync (sqflite ↔ Supabase)

- Write locally first (sqflite on Android) so the UI never blocks on network.
- Mirror to Supabase in the background via the repository layer.
- Use `updated_at` (Unix ms) for last-write-wins conflict resolution.
- Honour soft-deletes (`deleted_at`) — never hard-delete rows that have been synced.
- All Supabase tables must include `user_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE` on user-owned data.

> ⚠️ **`sqflite` does not support Flutter Web.** Before implementing the web target, the local storage layer must be replaced or made conditional. Options: Drift (with SQLite WASM on web), Sembast, or direct Supabase reads on web with no local cache. The `RepositoryProvider` abstraction is already in place — the change is contained to the data layer. Do not add web support to sqflite-based code; surface the decision to the developer first.

